(12, 'PROSPERITY CUP 2022: NEMBE CITY SCORE ELEVEN GOALS ', '<span>As the much awaited Bayelsa Governor Football Tournament, tagged \'The Prosperity Cup\' got into it\'s business stage, thirteen teams have booked their place in the next round of the competition, following victories on match day one played across eight centres on Friday.<br>The biggest victory came from the Nembe City Centre, as Nembe City pummeled their opponent, Kpogbokiri community, 11 goals to 2, in what is obviously, one of the biggest scoreline recorded in the history of the Governor\'s Cup since it\'s inception in 2015.<br>Peter Oyambo and Atebu B. both netted hat tricks, with Wisdom Vanman, Nengi, Abiola Oyekalum completing the rout in the second match that became a one sided game, in favor of the host.<br>The first game at the centre saw Etieama walk over Sangakubu, as the team failed to honour their fixture, same situation at the Tombia center in Yenagoa, where Oduduwa FC booked their place in the next round after walking over Redemption Fire FC.<br>However, in the second game, Grace Chapel FC defeated Ekpetiama community two nil, with Honest Bamson and Aaron Solomon finding the back of the net.<br>The Ekpetiama side attracted lots of support from Tombia community since they are neighbors and looked promising form the on set with lots of misused opportunities, but Honest Bamson\'s header in the 19th minute from Ebitimi Kalama\'s cross, and Aaron Solomon\'s beautiful slot from close range in the 72nd minute, ensured they progressed to the next round.<br>Joe Isuru could have reduced the deficit ten minutes to full time, but no thanks to his header which went some inches away from the woodwork after connecting from a free kick.At the BDGS centre, Agbura community defeated House of Hope FC three goals to two in the first game, as Swali Market saw off Experience Academy three-two in the second game, while at Opolo Centre, Bayelsa Palm FC defeated Niger Delta FC one nil, with NIIT defeating St. Joseph, Agudama 4-2 on penalties, after a one all draw at regulation time.<br>In other results, Land of Peace Church beat Divine Joy Ministry one goal to nil in the first game at the Okordia/Zarama centre, Potter House of God lost one four to Igbogene FC, Okoroma FC were two-one winners over Opu Nembe Community at the Okoroma Tereke centre, while at the Oporoma centre, Osokama community walked over Amaebide community.<br></span>', '09 May 2022', '09', 'May', '2022', '1fx.png', 1),
(13, 'PROSPERITY CUP: GOV. DIRI KICKS OFF COMPETITION ', '<span>Bayelsa Governor, Senator Douye Diri has called on the two hundred and six (206) participating teams at this year\'s Governor\'s Football Tournament, to imbibe the spirit of sportsmanship, fair play and ensure they give their best throughout the competition.<br><br>The Miracle Governor came out with this during the official kick off ceremony of the showpiece grassroots competition at the Samson Siasia Sports Complex in Yenagoa, on Monday.Governor Diri while declaring the competition open, described sports as an integral part of every society and expressed optimism that the tourney will not only curb youth restiveness, but create opportunities for exceptional players who may want to pursue a career in football.<br><br>He hinted that the state government was unable to host the competition last year, due to some unforseen circumstances.He however expressed elation that the entire state is now agog as the competition gets underway.<br><br>\"And I emplore all of you who are participating, and as you know that the game is fair play. I wish all of you the participating teams, good luck.\"<br><br>\"This is a competition that you need to put in your all, you wouldn\'t know those who are coming to watch you, you wouldn\'t know those who are coming to scout for players. This is a competition that can expose you nationally and internationally.\"<br><br>\"And for the ministry and the organisers, I will like to appreciate you, and thank you for ensuring that this year did not pass us by. This competition should have been held last year, but&nbsp; for unforeseen circumstances, we could not commence it last year.\"<br><br>In a remark, Youth and Sports Development Commissioner, Hon. Daniel Igali,&nbsp; attributed the success of the sporting sector to the commitment and support of the Governor to sports being a one time Commissioner for Sport in the State.<br><br>Earlier, Director General of the Prosperity Cup, Mr. Ono Akpe in his welcome address, highlighted some prospects of the competition, and&nbsp; thanked the Governor for the attention given to sports in Bayelsa state since he assumed office.<br><br>\"The tournament will run for six weeks and we anticipate that the final will be played on June 12. For now we have twenty centres across the State. Sixteen teams will emerge from the centres and will play until the final at this very stadium.\"<br></span>', '09 May 2022', '09', 'May', '2022', '9zuhp70hy4idrc3ajtdo1ffaac090dfc12bf50b4db5c4655b797.jpg', 1),
(14, 'LOC Prosperity Cup Congratulates Diri On 3rd Year Anniversary', 'The Local Organising Committee (LOC) of Nigeriaâ€™s largest grassroots football Tournament , the Prosperity Cup, has congratulated the Governor of Bayelsa state, Senator Douye Diri on his third year anniversary in office.<br><br>They also commiserated with the Governor on the demise of his father Pa Abraham Micheal Joseph Diri who passed on recently at the age of 88 years.The Director General of the tournament, Mr. Ono Akpe, in a statement issued and released in Abuja, described the Governor as a round peg in a round hole, whose support has brought tremendous development to the state especially in the area of sports and youth development which has earned him numerous awards including the recent Sportsville Governor of the Year Award.According to Mr Akpe, the state has received wide attention and has become the cynosure of all eyes from all sports stakeholders in the country and beyond, following honours and victories the state has recorded in different sporting event, since he assumed office in Febraury 2020.<br><br>The DG listed the victories of the stateâ€™s owned teams, Bayelsa United and Bayelsa Queensâ€™ victories at the 2021/22 edition of the Aiteo Cup in Benin, Bayelsa Queens winning the Super 6 of the Nigerian Women Football League last year, Bayelsa Unitedâ€™s promotion to the elite league for the first time since 2014, and Team Bayelsa breaking itâ€™s own record by finishing second at the National Sports Festival, after finishing third at the last edition, all during the Diriâ€™s his first 3 years as Governor, amongst other victories.<br><br>&nbsp;Ono Akpe stressed that the Governorâ€™s achievements in the sports sector in just three years was mind blowing, expressing his optimism that much more will be achieved after his eight year mandate.While congratulating the Governor, Senator Douye Diri, and his Deputy, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo on their successful three years in office, the LOC equally lauded the efforts and contributions of other stakeholders â€“ Youth and Sports Development Commissioner and Olympic Gold medalist, Hon Daniel Igali whose untiring efforts led to the successes.<br><br>Akpe thanked the Governor for his support and sponsorship towards sports and youth development including the Prosperity Cup: The SDD 15km marathon: The National Scrabble Championship: The National Wrestling Championships amongst othersHe also congratulated the Governor for also initiating the building of world class sporting facilities in the state most especially the proposed ultra modern stadium planned for the State which would bring more glory in the area of sports and youth development.<br><span><br>The DG while condoling Diri â€œon behalf of the LOC expressed deep sympathy with the Governor and the entire family of Diri on the demise of Papa at the age of 88. Losing a loved one no matter how old and especially a parent is always an emotional experience. We pray that the good lord will grant the soul of Papa eternal rest and comfort our dear Governor and his siblings in this time of griefâ€.</span>', '04 April 2022', '04', 'April', '2023', 'idd2ybqmdny2dgqammqa96eb925edbdf5bdacc15f217e87662ff.png', 1),
(15, 'Bayelsa: Prosperity Cup DG Commends Diriâ€™s Commitment To Sports Development', 'The Director General of the Bayelsa State Governorâ€™s Cup, Mr. Ono Akpe has commended the Governor of Bayelsa State, Douye Diri and Access Bank for sponsoring the inaugural state sports festival.<br><br>Mr. Akpe in a statement hailed Governor Douyeâ€™s drive towards sports development in Bayelsa State.Akpe a sports enthusiast and promoter, stated that Access Banks sponsorship of the Unity Games has further demonstrated the governorâ€™s commitment towards sports and the banks awareness of its social responsibility.<br><br>Ono while assessing the success of the Sports Festival explained that Governor Diri has used the instrumentality of his prosperity agenda and the stronger Bayelsa version to position the state on the true path of development.<br><br>The statement noted that the just concluded Bayelsa State Sports Festival is a pointer that there is peace and security in Bayelsa due to the regular engagement of Youths. â€œ from feelers the crime rate in the stare has reduced to a very low level, describing governor Diri as an â€œenabler of generational shift in sports growth and development.<br><br>He appreciated the Deputy Governor, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, Commissioner for Youth and Sports Development, Hon, Daniel Igali and the sponsors Access Bank for their foresight in ensuring the progress of sports in Bayelsa.He called on other corporate organisations and well meaning individuals to be emulate this initiative.<br><br>According to him, â€œGovernor Diri must be commended for his genuine love for sports and its development. He is indeed a square peg in a square hole when it comes to passion for sports and the all round development of the state.<br><br>â€œUnder his administration, Bayelsa State has maintained commanding positions in practically all spheres of sports in the country. This clearly shows that the governor is a lover of sports.<br>â€œBy giving the needed impetus for sports to thrive, he is at the same time creating opportunities for athletes to earn means of livelihood and contribute to the stateâ€™s economy.â€ he concluded.', '04 April 2022', '04', 'April', '2023', 'rcft83jhb1ktgrwcjehk8033e1e5c8c14db85d61cb6319f78037.jpg', 1),
(16, 'Prosperity Cup DG Lauds Gov Diriâ€™s Commitment To Sports Development ', 'Director General of the Bayelsa State Governorâ€™s Cup tagged the Prosperity cup, Mr Ono Akpe has given thumbs up to the Governor of Bayelsa State Senator Douye Diri and Access Bank for sponsoring the inaugural state Sports festival.<br><br>Mr Ono in a statement hailed the governorâ€™s drives toward sports development in Bayelsa State, stating that Access Bank Prosperity Unity Games has further demonstrated the governorâ€™s commitment towards sports.<br><br>According to the statement, Governor Diri has used the instrumentality of his prosperity agenda and the stronger Bayelsa version to position the state on the true path of development.<br><br>The statement notes that the just concluded Bayelsa State Sports Festival is a pointer that there is peace and security in Bayelsa, noting that due to the regular engagement of the minds of Youths crime rate has reduced tremendously, describing governor Diri as an â€œenabler of generational shift in sports growth and development.<br><br>He appreciated the Deputy Governor, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, Commissioner for Youth and Sports Development, Hon, Daniel Igali and the sponsors Access Bank for their foresight in ensuring the progress of sports in Bayelsa, calling on other corporate organisations and well meaning Bayelsans to be emulate this initiative.<br><br>According to him, â€œGovernor Diri must be commended for his genuine love for sports and its development. He is indeed a square peg in a square hole when it comes to passion for sports and the all round development of the state.<br><br>â€œUnder his administration, Bayelsa State has maintained commanding positions in practically all spheres of sports in the country. This clearly shows that the governor is a lover of sports.<br>â€œBy giving the needed impetus for sports to thrive, he is at the same time creating opportunities for athletes to earn means of livelihood and contribute to the stateâ€™s economy.â€ he concluded.<br>', '04 April 2022', '04', 'April', '2023', 'WhatsApp Image 2023-05-10 at 12.05.17 AM.jpeg', 1),
(23, 'PROSPERITY CUP 2023: 214 TEAMS TO BATTLE FOR N11m PRIZE MONEY IN NIGERIA\'S LARGEST GRASSROOT FOOTBALL TOURNAMENT', 'According to former Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger â€œAt a young age winning is not the most important thing, the most important thing is to develop creative and skilled players with good confidence\" ... <br><br>This quote by Wenger has been the strength of the organizers of the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Cup tagged the Prosperity Cup towards sustaining the tournament.<br>The Prosperity Cup has become the tonic that has lifted the soul of every player, coach, as well as community leader, as the tourney has engaged the minds of youths who are passionate and eager of earning a living through sports.<br><br>The tournament over the years has become a platform that birthed many players for the State owned team Bayelsa United, other Nigerian clubs and some European club sides.<br>Apart from producing players, the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Cup has also given young coaches the opportunity to manage teams in the competition , Kenneth Opukeme of Dreams Football Academy and Henserd FC goalkeeper trainer, Guembe Dennis are coaches who have been involved in the prestigious showpiece.<br><br><br>Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament has produced four different champions in 2015 Ewoama community of Brass Local Government Area won the tournament with 106 registered teams.<br><br><br>The Bayelsa State Government\'s quest for grassroots sports development continued in 2018 with an improved edition that witnessed 139 teams across the various local government areas seeking for glory, with Peretorugbene community of Ekeremor LGA emerging champions of the competition, then tagged Restoration Cup.<br><br><br>Okolobiri community in 2019 were crowned champions, with over 160 registered teams, in a final that saw the crÃ¨me de la crÃ¨me of Nigeria football converged in Yenagoa, including the Minister of Youth and Sports Development, Chief Sunday Dare, who described the competition as Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament.<br><br><br>Memories of the 2022 edition are still fresh in the minds of stakeholders, especially champions - Eternal Grace Ministry (EGM FC), following their sterling performance to win the trophy.<br>The Faith-based side started their campaign at the Okordia center with a 2-0 victory over Living Water International Christian Center, beat Igbogene community 2-1 in their second game, and when it seemed they will be knocked out, the Yenizengene based side piped Land Peace FC and Assemblies of God Church to book a place in the round of sixteen.<br><br><br>In one of the round of sixteen games decided in Sagbama, the champions - EGM FC beat Opuokun community 1-0 to move to the quarter finals, and defeated Okoroma Tereke FC of Nembe 2-0 to progress to the semis.<br><br><br>The semi final pairing produced enterprising football from the qualified teams, Anyama community of Ogbia, Agbere community of Sagbama, Odioma community of Brass and EGM FC of Yenagoa. Anyama Ogbia in the semi final failed to continue their fairytale run having stopped Movers FC of Otuasega from qualifying<br>Odioma community of Brass beat Anyama Ogbia 3-1 to qualify for the final, in a game tagged as the eastern derby, while EGM FC beat Agbere community 3-0 to advance to the final.<br>For EGM FC and Odioma community it was soul lifting to qualify for the final of Bayelsa State Governor\'s Cup for the first time with great prospects.<br><br><br>Two late goals gave EGM FC a 2-1 victory over Odioma FC of Brass despite taking the lead in the first half, an encounter watched by Bayelsa State governor Senator Douye Diri and his deputy senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo and other government functionaries at the Samson Siasia Stadium.<br><br><br>The 2022 edition had 210 registered teams with over 204 games played across the various local government. Over 510 goals were scored during the tournament, including six hat tricks.&nbsp;<br>Three players went head to head with the top scorer award late Ernest Pereowei who scored nine goals in four for his Bebelebiri community, Vincent Azipapu of Anyama community of Ogbia got nine in goals in seven matches, and Robinson Demeoru Ungo scored nine in two games. The best behaved team went to Peretorugbene community for their peaceful conduct, while EGM FC\'s goaltender won the best goalkeeper of the fiesta.<br><br><br>With the 2023 edition of Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots tournament the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Cup tagged the Prosperity Cup, already in the offing, football stakeholders are already in joyous mood, and cannot wait to witness the best of grassroot competition in the country.', '24 May 2023', '24', 'May', '2023', 'urxg2936ai80jetz39ys7e9c7e3af45d02cd0edd2cde2c6879e6.jpeg', 1),
(18, 'Bayelsa Governor\'s Cup final: EGM FC defeat Odioma FC to lift cup', '... get N5mln for the win\r\n<br>... Odioma FC get N2.5mln<br>&nbsp;... Agbere FC get N1m<br><br>The&nbsp; Eternal Grace Ministry (EGM) Football Club of Yenagoa have emerged champions of the 2022 Bayelsa Governor\'s cup, tagged, Prosperity Cup.\r\n\r\nIn the finals played at the main bowl of the Samson Siasia Sports Complex, Ovom, this evening, EGM came from a goal down to beat Odioma FC of Brass 2-1 in the game watched by Governor Douye Diri, his wife, Dr. Gloria, Deputy Governor, Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo and other top government functionaries.\r\n\r\nGoal Scorers for \r\nEGM F.C of Yenagoa, Onyema Ben and Stephen Harry, while Ayibakepreye Kumolayefa scored the only goal for Odioma F.C of Brass.<br><br>&nbsp;206 community-based teams participated in the tournament.\r\n\r\nAgbere FC of Sagbama LGA had earlier in the day won the 3rd placed after a 3-2 win over Ayama FC of Ogbia LGA.\r\n\r\nIn a speech, Governor Diri, who commended all the participating teams said he was happy that the competition would help discover talents and foster unity among the people.\r\n\r\nHe also commended the organisers particularly, the Director-General of the Governor\'s Cup, Mr. Onoriode Kevin Akpe , for a great show and that Bayelsa State is gradually becoming the centre of sports development in Nigeria.\r\n<br><br>&nbsp;\"It gives me great  pleasure today to be here physically to see the very satisfying and technical performance in this finals. This can be compared to any finals in the world, because, the standard of play is very high, and I can tell you that football is here in Bayelsa State.\r\n\r\nI congratulate you all of you who participated in this tournament, and as you know that sports, and in particular, football, is a unifier. This tournament has brought unity and peace to our State\",Gov. Diri stated.', '14 July 2022', '14', 'May', '2023', 'WhatsApp Image 2023-05-10 at 12.05.15 AM (2).jpeg', 1),
(22, 'Gov Diri Receives Tournament Official Jersey ', '<br>*** Bayelsa State Traditional Rulers Council Chairman Endorses Prosperity Cup***<br><br>&nbsp;The Director-General of the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament aka Prosperity Cup, Ono Akpe has formally presented Governor Diri with his official jersey of the Prosperity Cup. The presentation was made at the governorâ€™s home town Sampou in Kolokuma/Opokuma Local Government Area of Bayelsa State on Thursday, two days after the burial of Pa Abraham Joseph Michael Diri, the father of Governor Douye Diri.<br><br>&nbsp;Governor Diri in his response said he was elated with the presentation and preparations for the tournament made so far and thanked the organizers for their efforts, urging them to make this yearâ€™s tournament an outstanding showpiece. He affirmed&nbsp;that the cardinal objective of his administration is the pursuit of youth development through initiatives and sporting tournaments like the Prosperity Cup that empower and create jobs as launch pads for youths.<br><br><br>&nbsp;In another development the Chairman of the Bayelsa State Traditional Rulers Council, His Royal Majesty, King Bubaraye Dakolo, Agada IV and Ibenanaowie of Ekpetiama Kingdom has endorsed the Bayelsa Governorâ€™s Football Tournament and called on communities in the State to get involved in the fifth edition of the Prosperity Cup.<br><br>&nbsp;King Dakolo made the endorsement when a combined team of the LOC and Media/Publicity Committee of the Prosperity Cup led by the Director-General, Ono Akpe paid him a courtesy visit in his office in Yenagoa. The monarch noted that he was happy to receive the team in his office, stating that the gesture was indicative of the respect accorded traditional institutions in the Ijaw nation.<br><br>&nbsp;He noted that the traditional institutions will collaborate with the organizers of the showpiece to give the state a successful tournament, pointing out that he was elated to hear that the tournament has produced players who ply their trade in clubs here in Nigeria and in Europe. While commending the government and the organizers for sustaining the tournament all these years the Ibenanaowei of Ekpetiama Kingdom, urged Ijaw youths who are into sports to always promote the Ijaw culture wherever they find themselves in the world and prayed the organizers of the Prosperity Cup to inculcate these virtues in the players during the period of the tournament.<br><br><br>&nbsp;King Dakolo, called on corporation organizations, financial institutions, multinational oil companies, and intervention agencies to invest in sports development, describing sports as an agent of prosperity and unity. While giving his blessings to the tournament, the monarch equally pledged to reach out to other monarchs in the state to encourage their communities participate in the tournament while driving home the spirit of love, unity and peace.<br><br>&nbsp;He also commended the Prosperity Government for the peace initiatives carried out since its inception and believes the Prosperity Cup will add value to the peace the state is enjoying today. Earlier, Director-General of the Prosperity Cup, Mr Ono Akpe, thanked the Chairman of the Bayelsa State Traditional Rulers Council for giving his team audience despite his busy schedule.<br><br>&nbsp;Mr Ono Akpe pointed out that the visit had become imperative due to the respect and value his team has for traditional institutions, saying that society is incomplete without traditional institutions. He explained that the Prosperity Cup has helped to engage the youths in positive and lasting ways with the state usually recording zero crime in various local government areas during the tournament.<br><br><br>&nbsp;As the fifth edition is slated to kick off at the various local government areas later this month, Mr. Akpe noted that maintaining the standard of the most prestigious and largest grassroots football tournament in Nigeria would be the organizers utmost priority. He lauded the Prosperity administration for giving premium attention to youth and sports development in the state, stressing that Governor Diri\'s love for sports has given Bayelsa State international recognition.', '14 May 2023', '14', 'May', '2023', 'hjqjnjs8cgtnx5gn0w8bf1c0fdd835c0e969036f591954ae2197.jpg', 1),
(19, 'Why My Administration Invests In Sports â€“ Gov. Diri BY Amos Odhe.', 'Bayelsa State Governor, Senator Douye Diri, has explained why his administration prioritised sports development, saying it is an investment in youths of the state and a good avenue to discover and utilise their talents.Governor Diri also said that sports promotes the governmentâ€™s agenda of fostering peace and unity. <br><br>He spoke on Tuesday evening at the closing ceremonies of the Bayelsa Governorâ€™s Football Tournament otherwise known as the Prosperity Cup at the Samson Siasia Sports Complex in Yenagoa. A statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Daniel Alabrah, quoted him as saying that his administrationâ€™s investment in sports was yielding good results in the performance of the stateâ€™s athletes in national competitions in the last two years. <br><br>He noted that apart from the stateâ€™s football and basketball teams recording remarkable feats in national competitions in recent times, the Prosperity Cup with 206 participating teams is recognised as the largest grassroots football competition in Nigeria. He also recounted that the Governor Douye Diri National Scrabble Championship, which second edition ended on Sunday in Yenagoa, is the biggest scrabble competition in the country at the moment.He stated that through the football tournament, many talents were discovered by scouts that came from outside the country.He added that the stateâ€™s football club, Bayelsa United, will also be a beneficiary of the tournament.<br><br>Governor Diri appreciated his predecessors for the annual competition, saying his government had to embrace and sustain the lofty idea. The governor, who commended the organizers, said the standard displayed by the two teams in final game was very high and could be compared to any final match in the world. The stateâ€™s helmsman charged youths in the state to focus on discovering their talent and that they had no business with illicit drug activities or consumption. <br><br><br>His words: â€œWe believe that this is the best way to engage our youths. Through this tournament, a lot of talents will be discovered. Scouts have been here and I believe Bayelsa United will be the most benefiting club from the tournament.â€œI congratulate all the participating teams. As you know, sports and in particular football is a unifier. This tournament has brought together 206 teams across our state. It is the largest grassroots football tournament in this country.â€œIt has also fostered peace and unity in our state.<br><br><br>&nbsp;So, let me appreciate the founding fathers that introduced this governorâ€™s football tournament.â€œThis is a government of prosperity and those of you that have the skill, I am sure this tournament has exposed you to a brighter future. So try to discover where your talent is. You have no business with illegal drug activities, consumption and the attitudes that some youths exhibit. This is the right attitude to exhibit and you are very sure your government will support you.â€The governor expressed the optimism that the state will become the centre of sports and sports events in Nigeria.<br><br><br>&nbsp;He restated his call on individuals and companies operating in the state, particularly the oil producing companies, to take a cue from what the government was doing by investing in sports and the youths.The final match between Odioma community of Brass Local Government Area and Eternal Grace Ministry of Yenagoa ended 2-1 in favor of the latter, which took the winners N5m prize money while Odioma got N2.5m.Agbere community, which won the third place match against Anyama-Ogbia community by three goals to two got N1m while their opponents received N500,000.<span>Also speaking to journalists earlier, the Director â€“ General of the Prosperity Cup, Mr Onos Kelvin Akpe has commended and applauded the governor, Senator Douye Diri for sustaining the tournament, stressing that the 2022 edition has recorded huge success .<br><br><br>â€œFor the first time we brought two sets of scouts from Australia, France South- Africa and from Eastern Europe and they have selected players that are going to Europe in the next weeks to play their trade and that is the most exciting part of the event.Just like the governor, Senator Douye Diri has said, Bayelsa United will the most benefitting club from the tournamentâ€</span>', '14 June 2022', '14', 'May', '2023', '5e1o3wx4wpgnctd56lsk294894913eccc41f4ea758a31f8cba27.jpeg', 1),
(20, 'Coaches Hail Bayelsa State Government Over Continuous Investment In Sports', '.........As Governor Diri Woos Oil Firms On Sports Development in the State.<br><br>Coaches of participating teams in the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Cup tagged Prosperity Cup have hailed the organisers of the biggest grassroots tournament for the smooth organization.<span><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a>Enterprising Eternal Grace Ministry, EGM Fc of Yenagoa beat seasiders, Odioma FC of Brass 2-1 in a keenly contested final decided at the Samson Siasia Stadium Yenagoa.&nbsp;</span>Two late goals from Onyema Ben on 75 minutes and Steven Harry on 77 minutes canceled  Odioma Fc\'s Ayebadipreye Kumolayefa early goal as the prayer warriors cruised home with five million naira.<br><br>Earlier in the day, Agbere Fc Sagbama beat Anyama Fc of Ogbia 3-2 in the losers\' final to finish third in the tournament as Anyama Fc went home with five hundred thousand naira.In separate interviews shortly after the final, coaches of EGM Fc, Odioma FC, Agbere Fc and Anyama Fc commended  the organizers and the state government for bringing youths together during the tournament.Victorious coach of EGM Fc Micheal Felix said he was elated to lift the Prosperity Cup because they have worked hard in the last five years to get to this level, stating that the substitutes he made in the second half turned the game around in their favor .<br><br><br>He commended  governor Douye Diri for the event noting that the competition has engaged the youths meaningfully by exposing the players  to foreign scouts.Despite the defeat,Odioma Fc head coach, Daniel Solomon said he was not disappointed by the loss but attributed the defeat to a wrong  substitution made. The Coach noted that playing in the final of the Prosperity Cup was a plus for his lads having dominated Twon Brass centre in the preliminary round of the competition.Agbere Fc coach, Ebi Amula remarked that finishing third in the tournament which had over 200 teams has given Agbere community and Sagbama local government good publicity, explaining that his experience as a veteran in the game  played a crucial role in his team\'s  progress. <br><br><br>He appreciated the prosperity administration for giving premium attention to sports as well as using sports to combat socal vices among youths in Bayelsa.Anyama Fc\'s tactician, Ebiosuodo Appah said this year\'s prosperity cup has given his players exposure that would have been difficult to get, commending the organizers for being  transparent and supportive throughout the tournament.<br><br><br>He vowed  that Anyama Fc would come out smoking next year by winning the tournament, having gone this far this year.Declaring the tournament closed an elated Bayelsa State governor senator Douye Diri called on multinational oil companies and the organized private sector to invest in sports and not to leave it for government alone. <br><br><br>The state helmsman noted that with the stars he has seen in the tournament it was indicative that there are talents in rural areas, describing Bayelsa as the center of sports in Nigeria.While appreciating the sponsors of the 206 teams that took part in the showpiece the governor called on youths in the State to discover their talents and shun drug abuse reiterating  the government support for sports. <br><br><br>In attendance were the deputy governor,  Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, wife of the governor Mrs Gloria Diri, Member representing Ogbia Federal constituency in House of Representatives Hon.Fred Obua, speaker of the Bayelsa State House of Assembly Rt Hon. Abraham Igonbere, members of the state house of Assembly.Others are members of the Bayelsa executive council,LGA Chairmen, Chairman Civil Service commission and member, CAF medical Committee, Dr Peter Singabele, NFF representatives, State chairman People\'s Democratic Party Solomon Agwanana, Director of Sports, Sir Braveman Wodi, amongst other stakeholders&nbsp;<br><span><br>Hananeel JacksonAssistant media officer Prosperity Cup</span>', '14 June 2022', '14', 'May', '2023', 'xp91zz1lbvetqjnk2sxr79657644b537caadf10e9f7175180c7c.jpg', 1),
(21, 'Governor  Diri,  has restated that sports remains a cardinal focus of his government', '<br>Diri who made the declaration at the grand finale of the Bayelsa Governorâ€™s Football Tournament, popularly known as the Prosperity Cup, at the Samson Siasia Sports Complex in Yenagoa, stressed that his administration will continue to ensure the state is regarded as the home of sports in the country.<span>He assured more sporting events would soon be unfolded, urging youth and sports stakeholders to up their game and get ready for the competitions.<br><br></span>Diri described the just concluded national scrabble tournament which ended at the weekend in Yenagoa, where over two hundred players from all over the country participated, as one of the best events ever, going by the accolades he is receiving from stakeholders of the scrabble federation.<span>&nbsp;<br><br><br></span>Diri, who presented the trophy and prize money to the winners, Eternal Grace Ministry, (EGM) FC, pointed out that sport remains a veritable tool towards engaging youth in the state.<span>According to him, his government was willing to do more to ensure youths are encouraged to shun cultism, drug abuse, and other social vices, capable of ruining their lives.<br><br><br></span><span>The curtains of the fourth edition of the Bayelsa Governorâ€™s Football Tournament ended with hard fighting Eternal Grace Ministry, EGM FC of Yenagoa lifting the trophy in a spectacular fashion scoring two goals in two minutes to end the dream of Ocean boys, Odioma FC of Brass winning the tournament.<br></span><br><br>EGM FC of Yenagoa as the champion went home with a reward of five million naira, first runner up Odioma FC got a reward of&nbsp; N2.5 million naira ,third place winners, Agbere FC received one million naira (1,000,000) for their effort, while Anyama Ogbia, were rewarded with five hundred naira for their fourth place finish<br>', '14 May 2022', '14', 'May', '2023', 'jpy3eqro24zvy5hb8w98b3dd00c03f0384fc19fa21b4067d0bdb.jpeg', 1),
(24, 'PROSPERITY CUP 2023 OFFICIAL JERSEY PRESENTATION', 'The Deputy Governor of Bayelsa State, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, was on Thursday presented with the official jersey of the Governor\'s Prosperity Cup 2023.<br>The presentation ceremony, which was done at the Deputy Governor\'s Office, Government House, by the Chairman of the Organizing Committee, Mr. Onoriode Kelvin Akpe, through the Head of the Media Sub-Committee, Mr. Emmanuel Appah, indicates all is now set for the soon kick-off of the largest grassroots football tournament in the whole of Nigeria.<br><br>According to the Organizing Committee, the modalities for registration of all participating team and guidelines for the tournament have all been put in place, and would soon be communicated to the public through the appropriate channels.<br><br>Mr. Emmanuel Appah was accompanied by Mr. Kokobaiye Abeki, Ms Jennifer Ineye, and Mr. Vincent Joseph to make the official jersey presentation.', '26 May 2023', '26', 'May', '2023', 'u7rjws22ab05xf0ix8h49c5691f4271d666330ef66bf3738f08d.jpg', 1),
(25, 'TUC Boss Commends Gov Diri For Improved Prosperity Cup, Hails Organisers For the Innovations.', 'The chairman of the Trade Union Congress, Bayelsa State Council, Mr Laye Julius has commended the organizers of Bayelsa State governors cup tagged the Prosperity Cup for maintaining the standard from inception to date.<br><br><br>About 214 teams have registered for the showpiece which is the biggest grassroots football tournament in Nigeria as they battle for total prize money of N11 Million.<br>Mr Julius in an interview hailed the commitment of the organisers and the Bayelsa government for sustaining the tournament to the level where it has attracted international scouts to be involved.<br><br><br>The former Bayelsa State Football Association vice chairman noted that the competition has brought brotherhood and frenzy amongst communities and players in the state, stating that the competition has also exposed young Bayelsans internationally.<br><br><br>The TUC&nbsp; Chairman explained that the fiesta has not only empowered youths in the State but has provided a platform&nbsp; to be self-reliant&nbsp; as well as showcase their talents.<br>Mr. Julius asserted that the continuous increase in the number of participating teams was indicative of Bayelsans acceptance for the tournament.<br><br><br>He lauded the governor senator Douye Diri and his deputy senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo for giving priority to the development of sports in the State, pointing out that sports is incomplete in Nigeria without Bayelsa.<br><br><br>Eternal Grace Ministry EGM FC of Yenagoa are defending champions beating Odioma FC of Brass 2-1 to clinch the trophy at the Samson Siasia Stadium last year and watched by the Bayelsa State governor Senator Douye Diri and his deputy senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo and other government functionaries.', '29 May 2023', '29', 'May', '2023', 'fadjosmuukt9qoel5sd6ae827c28d73804069e3a490203d9356f.png', 1),
(26, 'Governor Douye Diri to kick of 5th Edition of Prosperity Cup 2023 with 214 teams', '***As Bayelsa Commissioner for Sports, Hon (Dr) Daniel Igali describes it as \"Africa\'s Largest Football           Tournamentâ€ ***\r\n<br><br>Bayelsa State Governor Senator Douye Diri is expected to lead members of the State Executive Council to kick-off of the much-awaited opening match of the Prosperity Cup Season 5 on Thursday at the Samson Siasia Sports Complex by 10am after the weekly prosperity walk, following the draws conducted on Tuesday 30th May.\r\n<br><br><br>Defending Champions Eternal Grace Ministry EGM FC of Yenagoa are set to defend their title as they take on Faith Comprehensive School in their group match at the Opolo Center.  \r\nThe defending champions will however trade tackles with Dream Boys of Odi in a ceremonial opening match on Thursday to whet the appetite of football lovers in anticipation of what is in store for the fans when teams lock horns across the state. \r\n\r\nEGM FC last year defeated Odioma FC of Brass 2-1 to lift Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football showpiece after a brilliant comeback from a goal down.<br><br><br>&nbsp;In the draws conducted in Yenagoa on Tuesday, 214 teams were grouped into twenty four different centers across the various Local Government Areas in the State with 5350 players set to take part in the spectacle.\r\n\r\nAt the Old Assembly Quarters Center , Kpansia FC  will face Shegbelit FC. Other matches include; Peremor Soccer Academy vs A.G Onopa FC; while Azikoro Youth Movement will have a date with the Nigerian Television Authority NTA, as two teams in Agbura, Agbura O.G FC and Agbura Young Stars will entertain fans in a local derby, while Dominion City of Azikoro will slug it out with Creek Haven Onopa.<br><br><br>&nbsp;Opolo Center will witness familiar fixtures when Yenagoa FC lock horns with Palm FC; Baptist Church FC of Ovom will square up against Ohaneze FC; Zola FC of Azikoro will battle House of Hope Schools FC; Rose of Sharon FC Opolo will take on God\'s Glory Ministries FC, Onopa FC welcomes Better Days FC of Swali.\r\n\r\nAgge Center in Ekeremor Local Government will see Famous Zion FC  taking on last yearâ€™s quarter finalist Agbayama FC, Bakiri FC will tango with Iyapregha Zion FC, while Ekperia are drawn bye.<br><br><br>&nbsp;The Ogbia zone is expected to rekindle old rivalries and friendships among communities in the three centers when they meet each other. At the Imiringi Center, New Evangel FC will take on Oruma FC; Golden Stars face Newcastle FC of Kolo; even as Okpoti 2 FC welcomes Aghalo FC of Kolo. At the Ogbia Center, Otuasega Movers FC will be looking to continue their dominance over Emeyal when they face Emeyal 1 FC.\r\n\r\nAt the Otuokpoti Center Anyama FC will hope to continue their fairytale run as they face neighbors Godâ€™s Promise FC of Otuedu; Okodi FC will entertain Ologi FC; Otuedu Community will battle Onubum FC while Elebele FC are drawn bye.<br><br>&nbsp;Hope Alive FC of Otueke will keep their hopes alive by winning a match in the Prosperity Cup for the first time at the Kolo Center when they file out against Star Boys FC of Opume; Christ Salvation Church FC of Ogbia will slug it out with Emeyal 2 FC; Apret FC of Imiringi entertains Amangala FC of Olobiri while Jerry FC are  on standby.<br><br>&nbsp;Okoloba FC at the Kaiama Center will battle Ekpuwari FC; Sampou Community face Sabagreia FC, Prosperity Cup tournament hopeful Dream Boys Football Academy are on standby, at the Opukuma center B.S.C.Y.C FC of Sampou will trade tackles with Bouturu FC of Igbedi.\r\n\r\nAt the Nembe Center the Nigeria Union of Journalist (NUJ) FC are drawn to be on standby, Kiri-Pogu Community FC will take on Nembe City FC, Igbeta-Iwoama FC will tackle Bayelsa State School of Health and Technology Otuogidi FC while Opu-Nembe FC are also on standby.<br><br><br>&nbsp;Odioma City at the Twon Brass Center will have Okpoma FC  versus Agbalakoko FC trading tackles; Canan FC takes on Twon Brass United while last year\'s finalist, Odioma City FC are on standby. Moses FC of Sangana Town at the Akassa Center welcomes Wagitia FC in their local derby; Williams of Sangana Town will face Amaogbo FC; Blessed Stars FC of Liama will come up against Fish Town FC.\r\n\r\nBayelsa United U15 who recently participated in the NPFL Laliga U15 in Ogun State will have a date with Salvation Favour Assembly at the Ogboloma Cente.<br><br><br>&nbsp;In Sagbama LGA Agbere FC were drawn bye as Agoro FC will tango with Bolu-Orua FC.\r\n\r\nDeclaring the draws ceremony open, chairman of the occasion, Sir Dr Peter Singable, urged the participating teams to abide by the rules of the competition.\r\n\r\nCommissioner for Youth and Sports Development, Hon (Dr) Daniel Igali in his remarks while thanking the governor for the genuine love shown in sports development lauded the Deputy, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo for his thoroughness towards handling issues, describing the fiesta as Africa\'s biggest grassroots football tournament.\r\n\r\nIn an address of welcome, Director General of the Prosperity Cup Mr Ono Akpe, promised an improved tournament that would produce more stars that would fly the Bayelsa flag outside the State.\r\n<br><br>&nbsp;He applauded Yenagoa Local Government Area for having the highest number of registered teams with a total of one hundred and thirteen teams.\r\n\r\nThe opening ceremony promises to be a spectacle as Governor Douye Diri will lead other top government functionaries including the Deputy Governor, National Assembly Members, The Speaker and other Assembly Members, the State Executive Council, Captains of Industry, Multinational Oil Companies, SWAN and sports lovers across the state to grace the show piece.', '01 June 2023', '01', 'June', '2023', 'fp125wjvt04m7cnqmlew4a1cce1d233386248388db19004e066c.jpg', 1),
(27, 'Gov. Diri Kicks Off 5th Bayelsa Governorâ€™s Cup', 'Senator Douye Diri on Thursday formally took the ceremonial kick off to herald the 5th edition of the Bayelsa Governorâ€™s Cup.\r\n\r\nThe tournament also referred to as â€˜The Prosperity Cupâ€™ is described as the largest grassroots football competition in Nigeria and Africa.\r\n\r\nGovernor Diri who performed the event at the Samson Siasia Sports Complex in Yenagoa was accompanied by the Deputy Governor, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo and a cast of top officials of the Bayelsa State government shortly after participating in the weekly Prosperity Jogging exercise.\r\n\r\nIn a remark, Commissioner for Youth and Sports Development, Daniel Igali said the tournament would have about 6,420 players participate.<br><br><br>&nbsp;He stressed that the products of such grassroots tournament had been recruited into the state owned Bayelsa United which campaigns in the Nigeria Premier League.\r\n\r\nA former member of the Nigeria Football Federation Executive Committee and Confederation of African Football Medical Committee, Dr. Peter Singabele gave thumbs up to Governor Douye Diri for sponsoring the competition, stating that it would ensure that more budding talents at the communities are discovered and groomed for stardom.\r\n<br><br><br>&nbsp;Earlier in a welcome remark, the Director General of the Prosperity Cup, Mr. Ono Akpe thanked Governor Diri for supporting the tournament which has continued to throw up young footballers including a player identified as Nestor who now plays in the Bosnian League and would be returning home to grace this yearâ€™s edition to motivate the younger ones to pursue their dreams.\r\n\r\nAkpe noted that the Governor increased the prize money from N5 million from previous editions to N11 million. <br><br>He stated that the competition is already attracting patronage from the private sector, urging multinational oil companies and the corporate world to support the tournament.\r\n\r\nIn the ceremonial opening game, a youthful _Bayelsa United_ Feeder team pipped defending champions, Eternal Grace Ministries (EGM) FC by a goal to nothing.\r\n\r\nA record 214 teams registered to take part in this yearâ€™s edition of the Bayelsa Governorâ€™s Cup with action expected to commence on Sunday, June 11th, 2023 with teams in Yenagoa Local Government Area battling for honours.\r\n\r\nA total prize money of 11 million are at stake in the compe', '02 June 2023', '02', 'June', '2023', '3rhi2g12oos33ciyxnxo1410cf20620787d23905306f6639da47.jpg', 1),
(28, 'Prosperity Cup Organizers Felicitate With Diri At 64 ', '<br>&nbsp;...He&nbsp; has demonstrated proven expertise in governance , planning, and political leadership.. .<br>The organisers of the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament christened the Prosperity Cup and have felicitated with Governor Douye Diri as he turns 64 years.<br><br><br>The organizers in a statement by Director General of the tournament Mr Ono Akpe, described Governor Diri as an urbane, cerebral leader of great value and a committed progressive that is concerned about the yearnings and aspirations of the people of the State.<br><br><br>According to the statement, the Prosperity Administration has made significant progress in infrastructure development, security, as well as, sports and the general welfare of citizens.<br>The statement extols the sterling and legendary contributions of governor Diri to the sustainable development of sports in the state in the last three years of&nbsp; his administration, stating that the governor\'s emergence is the best thing that has happened to the sports sector.<br><br><br>\"On behalf of all the outstanding young footballers, the brilliant coaches,&nbsp; the hardworking officials as well as the entire LOC of Nigerias\' largest grassroot football tournament, the Prosperity Cup, we salute His Excellency Senator Douye Diri on attaining the glorious age of 64 years\", the statement&nbsp; added.<br><br><br>It notes that Governor Diri&nbsp; has demonstrated proven expertise in governance , planning, and political leadership since he assumed office as the state\'s helmsman.<br><span>The statement wishes the governor more great strides and prays&nbsp; that God will bless him with wisdom and grant him success in his quest for nation-building and service to humanity\"<br><br><br></span>', '05 June 2023', '05', 'June', '2023', '5homfn47n9cwn3c5mb7t4e81e1f1cc6335a0dd808c35c398b66d.jpeg', 1);
