(29, 'More Partners Endorse Prosperity Cup as Teams in Yenagoa LGA Trade Horns...', '<br>The Prosperity Cup is receiving more and more support and appeal. The private sector led by Linkage Assurance is keying into the Miracle Governor, Senator Douye Diri\'s agenda of prosperity through sports by embracing the largest and most prestigious grassroot football tournament in Nigeria and bye and large Africa.&nbsp;<br><br><br>The Chief Executive Officer of Swiss Royal Grill, HRM Lady Evelyn Balogun has declared the group\'s unreserved support for the tournament and appreciates the recognition given her organisation by the LOC of the Prosperity Cup 2023.&nbsp;<br><br><br>Responding to the team led by the Deputy Director-General Deacon Emnanuel Appah after she was presented with a tournament customized jersey, the amiable CEO full of enthusiasm declared she will wear the jersey with so much pride and promised to attend matches as much as possible to give her support to the teams playing.&nbsp;<br><br><br>Deacon Appah, on behalf of the Director-General, Ono Akpe sent the high regards of His Excellency Senator Douye Diri to the CEO and her organization and commended her warm reception of the team.&nbsp;<br><br><br>Meanwhile teams are receiving their jerseys even as the first round matches of the Prosperity Cup will see teams from Yenagoa trading tackles with each other from the 11th of June. Kpansia FC will battle it out with Kadion Glorious School at the BDGS Center by 1pm. While Akaba Town 2 will tackle Ogbo United of Ikibiri by 3pm.&nbsp;<br><br><br>Other matches at the popular Maracana Stadium Kpansia will see Prime Wash FC sizing up Ogbolo FC in the first match just as Azikiro FC and St Patrick Church will bring out the best in their teams to pick a spot in the next round.&nbsp;<br><br><br>At the Old Assembly Quarters Kpansia FC and Shegbelegbe will fight for honours to the next round. Other centers will equally see entertaining football at it\'s best as Baptist Youth FC will meet Ohaneze FC at the Opolo School field followed by a match up between Zola FC and House of Hope School. At the Tombia Center, Ogu Colombia United and Dreams Academy will battle for honours just as Kpansia FC 2 will square up with Northern Strikers for the 2nd ticket in this center.<br><br><br>God\'s Grace Stars will pray to overcome BYS School of Nursing who will also expect to overrun their opponents. Polaku FC and Life Way Ministry will continue from where the 1st match left off in another winner takes it all duel at the Ogboloma Center. Not to be left out for a place in the second round are Kpansia Young Boys and GG Distinguished Ass. who will test each other\'s skills in the first match while Socials Int\'l FC and Ebis FC will hope to pick the 2nd ticket at the Igbogene Center.&nbsp;<br><br><br>Matches on the 11th will hold also at the Okordia Zarama Center with Agbia FC and Okolobiri FC leaving nothing to chance to get the first ticket in this center, while Biseni United will welcome Interact BY FC to the field in the second match.<br><br><br>Sunday the 11th June promises to usher in Season 5 of the Prosperity Cup with good entertaining football at all the centers.', '09 June 2023', '09', 'June', '2023', 'tzymkqk8v0irvw4179bu42d67375f8d67b37c51de89ad2f9802c.jpg', 1),
(30, 'Bayelsa State Governor\'s Cup Kicks Off Across 24 Centres', '.Yenagoa to host 16 matches on match Day One...\r\n\r\nHostilities will commence this weekend in the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament tagged the Prosperity Cup across the 24 centres in the State.\r\n\r\nBayelsa State Governor Senator Douye Diri last week took the symbolic kick-off of this year\'s spectacle at the Samson Siasia Stadium Yenagoa as Bayelsa United Feeders beat defending champions EGM FC by a lone goal.\r\n\r\n214 teams and 5350 players will be jostling for the 11 million naira price money for the showpiece starting from Sunday 11th June, 2023.\r\n\r\nDefending champions Eternal Grace Ministry EGM FC will begin their title defence against Faith Comprehensive School of Okutukutu by 1pm at the Opolo Center, while Rose of Sharon Ekeki will take on Godâ€™s Glory Ministries at 3pm both on Monday.\r\n\r\nBayelsa United Feeders on Tuesday will entertain Salvation Favour Assembly at the Ogboloma Center by 1pm. Bayelsa State School of Midwifery will face Grace Chapel of Agudama by 3pm as Yenizue-Gene United FC tacklesÂ Eleven Planet FC Okutukutu at 3pm in Tombia.\r\n\r\nThe opening fixtures in matchday one will see Kpansia FC play against Kadion Glamourous School by 1pm, while match 2 will have Akaba Town II Dynamics lock horns with Ogbo United,l Ikibiri by 3pm at the BDGS Center. Prime Wash FC at the Kpansia centre battle Ogbolo FC of Ogu at 1pm while Azikoro FC and St Patrick\'s Church will lock horns in the second match.\r\n\r\nFrom the fixtures we have in the Ogbia Centre, New Evangel FC welcoming Oruma FC, as Golden Stars FC of Ogbia tackles Newcastle FC at 3pm. At the Imiringi Centre, Vincent Azipapu Anyama FCÂ will square off with God\'s Promise FC Otuedu by 3pm  while first match of the day will see Okodi FC in action against Ologi FC.\r\n\r\nIn a related development, organizers of Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament, the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament tagged Prosperity Cup, have charged players and officials to show good conduct and morals during the competition.\r\n\r\nDirector-General of the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Cup, Mr. Ono Akpe, in a statement, said he was elated with the outpouring of encomiums from stakeholders in the state, saying the acceptance of the tournament has shown that this year\'s edition will be great.\r\n\r\nHe urged corporate organisations in Bayelsa to support this tournament, which has helped nurture the youths of the state to greater heights. Expressing his gratitude, he said, \"I want to thank Linkage Assurance, Century Group, Swiss Royal Grill, ,Aqualina Water for their support.\" He also thanked other interested partners like NCDMB, Ayalla Water, FIDO Water, Premuim Trust, and Sterling Banks for  their interest so far and hoped to see fruits of this interest soon. \r\n\r\n\"We look forward  to more support from other corporate gaints like the Oil Companies, Banks and others who operate in the state.\" Mr Ono remarked.\r\n\r\nHe charged coaches and players to be professional and civil and also embrace the spirit of sportsmanship as the tournament has alwaysÂ promoted peace in Bayelsa State.\r\n\r\nHe thanked the Governor Senator Douye Diri and his deputy Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo as well as the Commissioner of Sports, Daniel Igali for giving the Youths the platform to showcase their talents.\r\n\r\nOno Akpe  closed his statement with this remark, \"The Prosperity Government has consistently supported sports and youth development in the state, and this is highly commendable.\"', '11 June 2023', '11', 'June', '2023', 'edn1shyxwcyyi6ack7lmfcbfe9969bd55b0a23302040d8365ede.jpg', 1),
(31, 'PROSPERITY CUP 2023: Northern Strikers, Ohaneze Stars, Kpansia Young Boys, Others Emerge Victorious As 8 Teams Are Knocked Out On Match Day One.', '<span>&nbsp;**Defending Champions Begin Tournament Defence Today**<br><br>Zola FC of Azikoro, God\'s Grace Stars FC, Ogbolo FC of Ogu and Ohaneze FC are through to the next round of the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament tagged the Prosperity Cup.<br><br><br>The Prosperity Cup kicked off at the weekend with excitement across different centres in Yenagoa with a harvest of goals.<br><br><br>At Ogboloma Center, God\'s Grace Stars, Agbia, whitewashed Bayelsa State School of Nursing, 4-1 in the first game, as Polaku FC walked over Life Way Ministry in the second game. Ohaneze FC walked over Baptist Youth FC of Ovom in the first game at the Opolo center, to get a smooth passage to the next round, while Zola FC Azikoro were too strong for House of Hope School FC, beating them 3-0 in the second game to end their Prosperity Cup campaign.<br><br><br>At the Kpansia venue, Okaniba Arikparo and Toni Memory handed Ogbolo FC of Ogu a 2-0 victory over laundry Boys, Prime Wash FC in the first game, as Azikoro FC lost 3-0 to St. Patrick Church in the second game.<br><br><br>Shegbelegbe FC, in the first game at the Swali/Oxbow Lake Centre beat Kpansia IV FC 2-1 to advance to the next phase, at the Agbia Centre, Kpansia Young Boys piped Distinguished Association FC 2-0 as Social International FC humbled Ebi\'s FC of Biogbolo 3-1.&nbsp;<br>It was a goal feast for Okolobiri FC at the Okordia Center as Okolobiri thrashed Agbia 5-0 the highest scoreline in matchday one, while In the other fixture Biseni FC spanked Interact FC 4-2.<br><br><br>At the Tombia Center our reporter Opusam Ete reports that Ogu Colombia FC lost 0-1 to Dreams Academy FC, while the next fixture saw Northern Strikers booked their place in the next round winning 3-2 on penalties after a one all draw at regulation time.<br><br><br>Kpansia FC eased to the next round with a 3-0 win over Kadion Glamorous School at the BDGS Centre, as Akaba Town II lost 1-4 to Ogbo United Ikibiri in the other fixture.<br>Action continues today with interesting fixtures across Yenagoa. Defending Champions, Eternal Grace Ministry EGM FC will begin their title defence against Faith Comprehensive School at the Opolo Center by 1pm while Rose of Sharon FC Ekeki welcomes God\'s Glory Ministry FC at 3pm.<br><br><br>Kpansia 3 FC at the Tombia Center will entertain Deme Community FC in the first match of the day while St Michael Church FC tackles Experience Academy School FC, Grace Baptist Church FC of Agudama at the Ogboloma Center will host Igbogene FC.<br><br><br>JTF Headquarters FC Igbogene will battle&nbsp; Apostolic Church at the Ogboloma Center at 3pm, 6 0\'clock FC will be looking forward for a good result in the afternoon when they take on Akenfa FC, Amarata FC faces S.M.H.S of&nbsp; Okutukutu at 3pm.<br><br><br>The Nigeria Television Authority NTA FC will take on Azikoro Youth Movement FC at Swali Center, Peremor Soccer FC will face A.G Onopa in the first match of the day.</span>', '13 June 2023', '13', 'June', '2023', 'mmqsgny2z2q4rt04p75baeffd0c803971d3fefe6ed4bb8660d59.jpeg', 1),
(32, 'Prosperity Cup: Striker-Turned Goalkeeper Saves Four Spot Kicks...', '... As Anyama FC, Ogbolo FC, New Evangel FC Progress<br><br>Samuel Courage\'s heroic saves was the highlight of the game between Agbura FC and Akaba FC in the matchday four fixture, at the ongoing Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament tagged the Prosperity Cup.<br><br><br>The striker who stood in for his goalkeepers who were unavailable for the game, saved four spot kicks for his team, Agbura FC, in the second game at the Kpansia centre, and won 5-4, after a one all draw at regulation time.<br><br><br>It was a dramatic and intensive shootout that led to both teams taking eight spot kicks each, with Samuel Courage saving four of the kicks. The outcome saw Agbura FC progressed to the next round, despite fielding a natural player in between the sticks.<br>Earlier at the same centre, Ogbolo FC pummeled St Patrick Church 4-0, to move to the next phase of the Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament.<br><br><br>In other venues, Overcoming Lamb Assembly beat&nbsp; Sunboro FC 1-0 at the BDGS centre, as Divine Grace FC humbled Onopa Stars by three goals to one at the Swali Centre, while Creek Heaven All-stars progressed ahead of Dominion City FC of Azikoro.<br><br><br>Kilimanjaro FC at the Okordia centre beat Glorious FC 5-4 on penalties after a 1-1draw in the regulation time, while Yenegwe FC dispatched Glorious FC by three goals to nothing.<br><br><br>Opolo centre which has produced the highest number of goals so far in the tournament, failed to record more goals as United Star FC piped Hebrew Academy FC by a lone goal while N.A of Nursing and Midwifery AG/EKP, beat Apostolic Church II FC.<br><br><br>Ikolo FC also advanced to the next stage, winning 4-3 on penalties after a full time one all draw at the Tombia centre, despite scoring early in the game.<br><br><br>Last year semi finalist, Anyama FC of Ogbia at the Otuopoti venue cruised to a comfortable 3-0 victory of neighbors, God\'s Promise FC of Otuedu.&nbsp; Goals from Gogo Eluanatein, Agala Godgift and Felix Awilo, sealed the win for Anyama FC.<br><br><br>Earlier, Okodi FC beat Ologi FC 4-3 on penalties having played goalless at full time, while both games at&nbsp; the Imringi centre was decided on penalties. New Evangel FC secured a passage to the next round with a 5-3 win over Oruma FC, just as Golden Stars FC defeated Newcastle FC of Kolo 5-4 in the shootout after a one all draw.<br><br><br>Action returns tomorrow in different centres like Twon Brass, Okpokiri/Akassa Centre, Egbema-Angalabiri, Azuzuama, Oporoma, Amassoma, Agge and Ayamasa.', '15 June 2023', '15', 'June', '2023', 'fse8hqwobsbooh7jhb5b0731bdd9696aec95a2d06d44a4350654.jpg', 1),
(33, 'PROSPERITY CUP 2023: 10-MAN TANTUA FC STUN RESILIENT ADULAMA FC TO PROGRESS.....', '.....OSOKAMA FC, KALAOWEI-AMA FC, ODIOMA FC BOOK SECOND ROUND TICKETS<br><br>&nbsp;Southern Ijaw, Brass, and Ekeremor council areas, on Thursday, felt the pulse of the ongoing largest grassroot football competition in Nigeria, the Prosperity Cup, for the first time this season, as host communities came out in their numbers to watch the best of grassroot football.\r\n\r\nThe first game at the Amassoma centre witnessed one of the most intensed game in the competition so far, as both teams, Tantua FC and Adulama FC, defied the light showers and waterlogged pitch to express their intent to progress to the next round.\r\n\r\nHowever, Tantua FC proved to be the better side, defeating their opponents two goals to nil, despite having a player sent off for clumsy challenge.\r\n<br><br><br>&nbsp;From the blast of the whistle both teams were relentless, putting the defence line on their toes, and showcasing the best of attacking football, but it was Tantua FC that found the back of the net. A well taken free kick from 25 yards hit the crossbar, and attacking midfielder, Steamer Owoye was quick to tap in from close range to give his team the lead.\r\n\r\nAt the resumption, Adulama FC maintained their resolute to get back into the game, creating several opportunities, with winger, Bugro Kelvin, close on two to three occasions in getting the equalizer, but Tantua FC goalkeeper, Alaowei Prosper remained vigilant with his tremendous saves, until Steamer Owoye scored his second goal with a well taken lwo-level free kick, to put the game to bed.<br><br><br>&nbsp;The second game at the Amassoma Centre saw Amassoma United winning two goals to one against one of the youngest sides paraded in the competition, Oguonama FC. Adobu Tony scored from close range after a cleared ball came his way to put his team ahead.\r\n\r\nOguonama FC had an opportunity to level via penalty, and skill forward, Temple Favour missed from the spot, before Adobu Tony completed his double from a set piece with fifteen minutes left.<br><br><br>&nbsp;Oguonama FC still maintained pressure and scored deep into added time.\r\n\r\nIn other results, George Super of&nbsp;Moses FC of Sangana scored a brace against Wagitia FC in the matchday five at the Akassa Centre to put his side Moses FC into the next round of the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament christened the Prosperity Cup, while the second group saw William FC of Sangana walked over Amaogbo FC.\r\n\r\nAt the Ayamasa centre Crusaders FC crushed Peretoru I FC three nil, as&nbsp;Larama FC beat Isampou FC 4-2 on penalties after goalless draw at regulation time.\r\n\r\nThe only game at the Egbema-Angaabiri centre in Ekeremor Local Government Area, saw Azagbene Federated FC eased out Tuboama Community by a lone goal. In Twon Brass, Kurotei FC and Odioma City FC settled for a one all draw, but Odioma FC progressed 5-3 on penalties, while the second game between Canaan FC and Twon-Brass United, was shifted till today, Friday.\r\n<br><br><br>&nbsp;The matchday five fixtures for Azuzuama centre between Olou United FC, Lobia I and Sampou Sound FC, and Ayiscos FC, Ogboinbiri against Igbematoru FC, as well as the only game at the Agge centre between Osunmaibio Community FC and Agbayama FC Ogbotubu, will all take place today, Friday, including games for matchday six.<br><br><b>&nbsp;MATCHDAY 5 RESULTS</b>\r\n<br><br><b>&nbsp;TWON-BRASS CENTRE</b>:<br><br>&nbsp;*\r\nKurotei FC *1* vs *1* Odioma City FC\r\n(Odioma City wins 5-3 on penalties)<br><br><b>&nbsp;OGBOKIRI, AKASSA CENTRE:</b><br><br>&nbsp;Moses FC, Sangana Town *2* vs *0* <br>Wagitia FC \r\nWilliam FC, Sangana T.  *3* vs *0* Amaogbo FC\r\n(William FC walked over Amaogbo FC)	<br><br>&nbsp;<b>EGBEMA-ANGAABIRI CENTRE</b>:<br><br>Tuboama Community *0* vs *1* Azagbene Federated Comm.\r\n<br><br>&nbsp;<b>OPOROMA CENTRE:</b><br><br>&nbsp;Ayama Ijaw FC *0* vs *3* Osokama FC<br>&nbsp;Kalaowei-ama FC *0* vs *0* Luduon FC 		\r\n(Kalaowei-ama wins 7-6 on penalties)\r\n<br><br><b>&nbsp;AMASSOMA CENTRE:</b><br><br>&nbsp;Tantua FC *2* vs *0* Adulama FC <br>&nbsp;Amassoma United *2* vs *1* Oguonama FC <br><br><b>&nbsp;AYAMASA CENTRE:</b><br><br>&nbsp;Peretoru I FC *0* vs *3* Crusaderâ€™s Feeders FC\r\n<br>Isampou FC *0* vs *0* Larama FC		\r\n(Larama FC wins 4-2 on penalties)\r\n<br><br>&nbsp;', '16 June 2023', '16', 'June', '2023', 'o93y7xx0g5idqwnnvwgh07673011ebd33e60f6c796fd72d15c50.jpg', 1),
(34, 'PROSPERITY CUP: UPSET AS \'SCHOOL BOYS\' SEND COMMUNITY TEAM, IYC, PACKING ON MATCHDAY SIX', 'It was a happy day for two of the tertiary institutions participating at the ongoing Nigeria\'s largest grassroot football competition, the Prosperity Cup, on Matchday six, Friday, as the Amassoma centre saw the Niger Delta University FC, and the College of Health and Sciences FC, book their passage to the next round of the tournament.<br><br><br>The major upset was in the second game when the College of Health and Sciences came from a goal down to defeat the Ijaw Youth Council, Ogboin Clan two goals to one.<br>From the blast of the whistle, the IYC team showed class and experience in their playing pattern, which led to a couple of attempts, before striker, Lawyer, scored a beautiful header in the 14th minute from a corner kick to break the deadlock.<br><br><br>In the second half, Egberi Ayibatonye\'s strike in the 74th minute made it one all. The equalizer seemed to change the wind of the game, especially with the introduction of aggressive forward, Iwhi Ufuoma, who didn\'t stayed on the pitch for too long before scoring the winning goal for the school team with five minutes left.<br><br><br>Earlier, another tertiary side, Niger Delta University FC were one nil winners over Pere Ogbo FC, to advance to the next round, and will meet the College of Health and Sciences on Sunday, at same venue.<br><br><br>In other results of Matchday 6, Gasof FC of Oweikorogha lost 1-2 to Otuan FC in the first game at the Oporoma centre, while Oporoma FC defeated Aguobiri FC 3-1in the second game. Okpoti II FC of Ogbia humbled Agholo United of Kolo three nil at the Imiringi centre, as Emeyal I FC crashed out after losing two nil to Otuasegha Movers FC.<br><br><br>At Twon Brass, Okpoma Agbalakoko defeated Egweama FC by one nil, while at the Akassa Centre,&nbsp;Blessed Stars FC of Liama were humbled with a 1-4 defeat by Fish Town FC.<br>The Matchday 5 game rescheduled for Friday at Agge centre saw Osunmaibio FC winning&nbsp; Agbayama FC 5-4 on penalties after a one all draw at full time.<br><br>MATCH DAY SIX (6) RESULTS <br><br>Friday 16-06-2023<br><br>*OPOROMA CENTRE:<br><br>*Gasof FC, Oweikorogha *1* vs *2* Otuan FC<br>&nbsp;Oporoma FC *3* vs *1* Aguobiri FC<br>*AMASSOMA CENTRE:<br><br>*Pere Ogbo FC *0* vs *1* NDU FC&nbsp;<br>College of Health &amp; Sciences *2* vs *1* IYC FC, Ogboin Clan<br><br>*IMIRINGI CENTRE:<br><br>*Okpoti II FC, Ogbia *3* vs *0* Agholo United FC,<br>&nbsp;KoloEmeyal I FC *0* vs *2* Otuasegha Movers FC*<br><br>TWON-BRASS CENTRE:<br><br>*Okpoma Agbalakoko *1* vs *0* Egweama FC<br><br>*OGBOKIRI, AKASSA CENTRE:<br><br>*Blessed Stars FC, Liama *1* vs *4* Fish Town FC<br><br><br>*RESCHEDULED MATCHDAY 5 RESULTS*<br><br>*BRASS CENTRE:&nbsp;<br><br>Canaan FC *4* vs *0* Twon Brass United<br>*AGGE CENTRE:<br><br>*Osunmaibio FC *1* vs *1* Agbayama FC(Osunmaibio FC wins 5-4 on penalties)<br><br>AZUZUAMA CENTRE:<br><br>Sound City FC, Sampou *3* vs *0* Olou United FC, Lobia&nbsp;(Sound City FC walked over Okou United FC)Ayisco FC, Ogboinbiri *3* vs *1* Igbematoru FC<br><br>*MATCHDAY SEVEN (7) FIXTURES*<br><br>Saturday 17-06-2023<br><br>*EGBEMA â€“ANGALABIRI CENTRE:<br><br>*Azagbene Fed. Comm. *vs* Young Dons FC,<br>&nbsp;Koromotory Comm. 1pmClough Creek FC, Egbema-Ang. *vs* Egbema-Ang. FC 3pm<br><br>*AZUZUAMA CENTRE:<br><br>*Alokobio FC, Lobia II *vs* Sound City FC 1pm<br><br>Azuzuama FC *vs* Ayisco FC, Ogboinbiri 3pm<br><br>*AGGE CENTRE:<br>*Osunmaibio FC *vs* Amazor Community FC 1pm<br>Bakiri Comm. FC *vs* Agge Community FC 3pm<br><br>*AYAMASA&nbsp; CENTRE:<br><br>*Pinakiri Zion, Torugbene II *vs* Crusaders FC 1pm<br>Peretoru II FC *vs* Larama FC 3pm<br><br>*OTUOKPOTI CENTRE:<br><br>*Otuedu Comm. FC *vs* Onuebum FC 3pm<br><br>NEMBE CITY STADIUM (OGBOLOMABIRI) Kiri-Pogu Owokiri *vs* Opu-Nembe FC 1pm<br><span><br>BOYCOTECH Otuogidi *vs* NUJ Bayelsa 3pm</span>', '17 June 2023', '17', 'June', '2023', 'vezuvvvriwekkcuul4rocfb10ab38db51f314407a2103008486c.jpg', 1),
(35, 'Imiringi Natives Heap Praises on Prosperity Cup Organizers', '****applauds Gov Diri For Investing in Sports***\r\n\r\nThe people of Imiringi in Ogbia Local Government Area of Bayelsa State have given thumbs up to the organisers of Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournamentÂ  Bayelsa Governor\'s Football Tournament for citing one of the Ogbia centres in Imiringi Community.\r\n\r\nImiringi, Kolo and Otuopoti are three centres settled by the organisers of Prosperity Cup in Ogbia LGA among the 24 centresÂ  across the State with 214 teams seeking for prosperity cup.\r\n\r\nSome of the locals in separate interviews said they are pleased with the improved level of organization and competitiveness amongst the teams in this yearâ€™s edition.\r\n\r\nA former player Mr. Akalisuo Lapahe, hailed the organizers for bringing Imiringi community, stating that they are happy with the respect accorded to the community and that they are ready to provide security for officials and participating teamsÂ  as a way of saying thank you.Â \r\n\r\nHe commended the Governor Douye Diri and his deputy senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo for giving Bayelsa youths a veritable platform to showcase their potential to the world and foreign scouts and that they are capable of competing with their peers anywhere in the world.\r\n\r\nA native Mr. Obhuo Philip asserted that the 5th edition of the showpiece is timely following one of the son\'s and product of the Prosperity Cup then Restoration cup Robert Mizo brilliant outing in the just concluded Nigeria Premier Football League NPFL season where he scored nine goals in the campaign.\r\n\r\nHe aligned himself with the shared prosperity of the Prosperity government and continuous peace enjoyed in the State, pointing out that since the commencement of the tournament more especially the Imiringi centre that no crime has been recorded in the community due to the love the people have for football.\r\n\r\nAlso, a retired referee, Wariso Imorobebi, applauded the organizers for engaging professional referees, saying the gesture brought more credibility to the tournament.\r\n\r\nImorobebi described the turn out of fans in Imringi community as the best you get in any centre in Bayelsa State, adding that he is hopeful that more Robert Mizo, Gabriel Biriduba and Okardi Jnr would be discovered at the end of the tournament.\r\n\r\nHe noted that since governor Diri assumed power as the state helmsman that the governor has given sports a new dimension.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, action returns on Monday inÂ the Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament at the Kolo Centre Apret FC Imiringi will battle Amangala FC of Oloibiri by 3p, while Azagbene Federated at the Egbema-Angaabiri Centre will face Egbema-Angaabiri FC.\r\n\r\nThe other fixture Ayamasa Centre will see high flying Crusader\'s Feeders square off with Larama FC', '19 June 2023', '19', 'June', '2023', 'z4efw9y7jkpwngru89clc1b38ce295491aacc6e1a2bfcb7e4e0d.jpg', 1),
(36, 'PROSPERITY CUP: NIGERIAN UNION OF JOURNALISTS, THREE OTHER TEAMS BOOK ROUND 32 SPOT', '<br>The Nigerian Union of Journalists Football team have progressed to the Round of thirty-two (32) following their two nil victory over Bayelsa State College of Health, Otuogidi.<br>Despite coming into the competition as debutants, the journalists have proved not to be minnows, but contenders for the title, and will battle Kiri-Pogu Owokiri FC for the Champions from Nembe Centre.<br><br><br>Azagbene Federated Community on Sunday also qualified for Round of 32 after defeating Egbema Angalabiri FC on matchday nine. The team won 5-3 on penalties after a goalless draw at full time.<br><br><br>Agge FC defeated Osunmaibio FC one nil to progress to the Round of 32, while Crusaders Feeders humbled Larama FC three nil to progress to the Round of 32 from the Ayamasa centre.<br><br><br>Southern Ijaw, Ogbia and Brass is expected to be wrapped up this week, while next week, Sagbama, Kolga and Yenagoa will complete their preliminary stages.<br><br><br>RESULTS<br>MATCH DAY NINE (9)								19-06-2023<br><br>EGBEMA-ANGALABIRI CENTRE:Azagbene Federated Community FC 0 vs 0 Egbema Angalabiri FC(Azagbene Fed. Comm. wins 5-3 on penalties)Azagbene Fed. Comm qualifies for Round of 32<br>AGGE CENTRE:Agge FC 1 vs 0 Osunmaibio FCAgge FC qualifies for Round of 32		<br>AYAMASA CENTRE:	Crusaders Feeders FC 3 vs 0 Larama FC	Crusaders Feeders FC qualifies for Round of 3<br>KOLO CENTRE:&nbsp;Amangala FC, Oloibiri 1 vs 2 Apret FC, Imiringi', '20 June 2023', '20', 'June', '2023', 'xkhtqhoaxlv3lhkb821zf1fbfaca040c94714af387dd6d525f26.jpeg', 1),
(37, 'PROSPERITY CUP: AMASSOMA UNITED BOOK ROUND OF 32 SPOT VIA ELECTRIFYING SHOOT-OUT', '<br>.......AS ATTENTION SHIFTS TO SAGBAMA, KOLGA<br><br>The matchday ten fixture of the ongoing Nigeria\'s largest grassroot football competition, the Prosperity Cup, between Amassoma United and Niger Delta University FC, witnessed one of the most intensed game this season filled with intrigue and suspense, due to the energy and dexterity displayed by both teams in their quest to claim the number one spot at the Amassoma Centre.<br><br>The Amassoma Secondary School field was the usual host for thr games but due to the incessant downpour, the organisers chose the NDU school field, and the atmosphere was suitable for the game, as students and other football enthusiasts were in their numbers to cheer the traditional teams to victory.<br><br><br>Niger Delta University FC drew first blood in the 14th minute, after Amassoma United\'s goalkeeper, Obichebe Precious, tried to find his teammate, unfortunately the ball met winger, Amassoimo Ebi of NDU FC who beautifully lobbed the ball beyond the reach of the goalkeeper who was already out of his line.<br><br><br>Amassoma United mounted pressure in search for an equaliser, and thier chase paid off when they won a penalty in the 32nd minute, and Zitua Stephen stepped up to convert it neatly, to draw level.&nbsp;<br><br><br>At the resumption, the struggle continued as both teams matched each other for size, but it was NDU\'s Ataiwaere Efeigho who had the closest opportunity to send his team through with a well taken free kick, however, goalkeeper Obichebe Precious was vigilant to parry the ball away, with the game ending in a stalemate.<br><br><br>In the shootout, Amassoma United lost two spot kicks, but Niger Delta University failed to seal the victory with their last spot kic to qualify for the Round of 32, hence the shoot out went to the death.&nbsp;<br><br><br>Bibi Ebi Jerry of NDU FC was the culprit as he blew his kick over the top of the cross bar, while Nelson Oyindoubra converted his penalty to send his teammates and the entire supporters of his team in to a wild jubilation.<br><br><br>Both teams played twelve spot kicks each, but it ended 10-9 in favour of Amassoma United.<br>Chairman, Sports Committee of the Niger Delta University, Professor Diepreye Elliot, during an interview, expressed his gratitude to the Governor, Senator Douye Diri, for his support to the tournament which has brought a lot of youths who are passionate about football together, adding that one sure way to captivate youths of Bayelsa was through the sports.<br><br><br><br>Professor Elliot who witnessed the entire game, however decried lack of sporting facilities as the major challenge faced by athletes and coaches, as he called on authorities to provide state-of-the-art sporting facilities, which will help catapult Bayelsa athletes to greater heights.<br>In other results Moses FC of Sangana book their Round of 32 spot after beating Fish Town FC one nil in the last game at the Akassa centre, while winners will emerge at the Brass and Oporoma centres today, Wednesday.<br><br><br>Meanwhile, attention will shift to Sagbama and Kolokuma Opokuma council areas as they set to taste the competition for the first time this season. The Sagbama centre which has been moved to Ebedebiri primary school will see Agoro FC take on Bolo-orua United at 1pm, while Angalabiri United will host Akede United at 3pm.<br><br>At the Opokuma centre, B.S.C.Y.C FC, Sampou will tackle Boutoru FC, Igbedi at 1pm, Temple Owonaru FC faces Igbainwari FC at 3pm, as Okoloba FC hosts Ekpuware FC at the Kaiama Center at 3pm.<br><br><b>MATCHDAY 10 RESULTS</b><br><br><b>AMASSOMA CENTER:</b><br><br>Amassoma United 1 vs 1 NDU FC(Amassoma Utd wins 10-9 on penalties)Amassoma United qualifies to Round of 32<br><br><b>AZUZUAMA CENTRE:</b><br><br>Ayisco FC Ogboinbiri 0 vs 0 Alokobio FC Lobia II(Ayisco FC Ogboinbiri wins 3-1 on penalties)<br>AKASSA CENTER:Moses FC 1 vs 0 Fish Town FCMoses FC of Sangana qualifies to Round of 32<br><br><b>MATCHDAY 11 FIXTURES</b><br><br>&nbsp;Wednesday 21/06/23<br><b>SAGBAMA CENTRE</b><br><br>&nbsp;moved to Ebedebiri Primary School&nbsp;Agoro Fc vs Bolo-Orua 1pmAngalabiri United vs Akede United Fc - 3pm<br>OPOKUMA CENTRE:B.S.C.Y.C FC, Sampou vs Boutoru FC, Igbedi 1pmTemple owonaru fc Vs Igbainwari FC - 3pm<br>KAIAMA CENTRE:Okoloba FC vs Ekpuware Fc - 3pm<br>KOLO CENTER:&nbsp;Hope Alive Fc vs Emayel II Fc&nbsp; - 11amApret Fc Imirngi vs Jerry FC, Ogbia - 1pm', '22 June 2023', '22', 'June', '2023', 'h44k6c6au21gtea5bw0e08a8b910481a62e1fd5cd62b6afbe9f0.jpg', 1),
(38, 'Prosperity Cup: Defending Champions EGM FC Crash Out', '<br>&nbsp; * Polaku FC, Ohaneze FC, Biseni United, Otuasega FC, Apret FC Progress To Round 32**<br><br>Eternal Grace Ministry EGM FC, who are the defending champions of Nigeria\'s largest grassroot football competition, the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament have been dumped out of the tournament after suffering a stunning 6-5 defeat on penalties by less fancied side, Rose of Sharon FC.<br><br><br>The defending champions EGM FC mounted so much pressure on their opponent from the first half all through the entire encounter, but were unable to find the back of the net, as the game ended in a goalless draw in regulation time at the Opolo centre, were they crashed out through penalties.<br><br><br>EGM FC became more nervous and increased their pressure after the break and kept pushing forward, but despite dominating the second half, they were curtailed by the vigilant Rose of Sharon FC.<br><br><br>The tournament\'s fourth holder of the title, failed to defend the trophy despite trouncing \'School Boys\', Faith Comprehensive Secondary School 15-0 in their opening fixture.<br>Rose of Sharon FC\'s victory could be likened to Okodi FC upset against last year\'s semi finalist Anyama FC of Ogbia who lost one nil to neighbors Okodi FC at the Otuopoti venue.<br>Elsewhere in the competition at the Okordia centre, Polaku FC beat God\'s Grace Stars FC 3-2 just as Biseni United defeated&nbsp; Okolobiri FC 3-0 in same centre.<br><br><br>Ohaneze FC also progressed to the next phase with a 2-1 victory over Zola FC, NMA FC at the Okordia centre kept their hopes of moving to the money spinning stage as they beat another faith based organization City Zuph FC 4-3 on penalties after an entertaining two all draw.<br><br><br>Igbogene FC at the Ogboloma centre humbled JTF H/QTRS 3-0, Ogbolo FC at the Kpansia centre eased out Agbura FC 2-1, Dream Academy at the Tombia centre pipped Northern Strikers 3-1 to end Northern Strikers fairytale run in the competition, while Kpansia 3 FC in the second game beat Experience Academy by a lone goal.<br><br><br>Action returns tomorrow in matchday thirteen of Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament across different centres.', '23 June 2023', '23', 'June', '2023', 'xn1851z7qiq1qoebheh9f69bad3c43a29bb573596af4494c9f0f.jpeg', 1),
(39, 'Prosperity Cup: Ikolo\'s Everton Academy FC Coach Upbeat of Winning Tournament', '*Appreciates Gov Diri and Organizers For Improving Competition Standard**_\r\n\r\nEverton Academy FC of Ikolo coach, Prosper Dagilo says he is optimistic that his young team will win this year\'s Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament tagged the Prosperity Cup.\r\n\r\nThe team nicknamed Evertonians have been the revelation of the competition, winning three games out of three with the latest win against Overcoming Lamb Assembly FC to seal a place in the round of 32 of the Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament.\r\n\r\nIn an interview, Coach Prosper, said his target in the Prosperity Cup is to win the competition despite parading one of the youngest squad in the tournament, pointing out that determination and commitment has shown in their current state of the competition.\r\n\r\nHe noted that he was building a team that would be a feeders to many clubs in Nigeria and Africa, describing the encounter against Overcoming Lamb Assembly FC as the most difficult side the lads have played against so far.\r\n\r\nThe Everton Academy gaffer who is also a player in the ongoing competition, explained that the reason behind the formation of the Academy was to take the lads out of the streets and out of engagement in drug abuse, and for them to earn a living through football, saying that the Academy has impacted lives positively since it was founded in 2019.\r\n\r\nWhile appreciating the Almighty God for progressing to the round of 32, the Everton Academy coach thanked the Governor for improving the standard of the competition, especially the prize money and the branded jerseys.\r\n\r\nHe also hailed the organizers of the Prosperity Cup for the innovation in the tournament as well as the increase in the number of the participating teams from 209 to 214 registered teams.\r\n\r\nSimilarly, the final preliminary matches for the Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament has been concluded at the Opolo centre, as Onopa FCÂ spanked United Stars FC 2-0 while in the other rescheduled game at the Tombia centre De Grace FC secured a passage to the 32 a with 4-2 victory over Okordia FC after a one all draw in regulation time.\r\n\r\nHostilities will resume this weekend in the round of 32 across different centres after a three day match rest.', '28 June 2023', '28', 'June', '2023', 'pie7i8kbnkon5uceiz4af2a3e3d7deca8e9ffa7c3b46d21bda27.jpg', 1),
(40, 'Bayelsa Governor\'s Cup 2023: 182 Matches, 499 Goals In First Round As 32 Teams Qualify For 2nd Round.', '<br>**Tournament Revelation Everton Academy Ikolo Face Tough Tie**<br><br>Governor Douye Diri few weeks ago took the kick-off that has heralded a two-week season of wonderful football skills in Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament tagged the Prosperity Cup. Since commencement of the showpiece the progress of the competition has continued to be the most discussed topic in the media within and outside the state.<br>Bayelsa United Feeders in the ceremonial kick-off beat defending champions Eternal Grace Ministry EGM FC 1-0. The fixture was witnessed by governor Douye Diri, his deputy Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo and other top government functionaries.<br><br><br>After the preliminary matches in Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football tournament the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament christened the Prosperity Cup 32 teams have been separated from the 214 that registered for the championship.<br><br><br>According to a release by Nwankwe Diseye, Chairman of the Technical Committee, 182 matches have been played in 24 centres across the eight local government areas.<br>One hundred and eighty two (182) teams have been eliminated from the spectacle including the defending champions Eternal Grace Ministry, EGM FC while four hundred and ninety nine (499) goals have been scored so far in the tournament with Opolo and Okordia Centres producing the highest number of goals.<br><br><br>Last year the Prosperity Cup recorded 513 goals in 205 games as it witnessed three persons contending&nbsp; for the golden boot award.<br>Late Ernest Pereowei scored nine goals, Azibapu Vincent of Anyama FC nine goals, Demeoru Ungo Robinson nine goals in two games for Azatitor FC while best behaved team went to Peretorugbene Fc.<br><br><br>Spectators have continued to enjoy good football and off the pitch excitement especially in Imiringi, Twon Brass, B.D.G.S, Swali and Ogboloma Centers.<br>Yenagoa produced eight centres due to the number of registered teams, Opolo, Kpansia, Swali/Ox-Lake, BDGS, Tombia, Okordia and Agbia. Brass LGA has Twon Brass and Ogbokiri/Akassa Centres,&nbsp; Ogbia LGA produced Imiringi, Kolo and Otuopoti Centers, while Ekeremor LGA has Ayamasa, Agge and Egbema-Angalabiri as Centres.<br><br><br>Sagbama has two centres Ebedebiri and Sagbama Town, Nembe with one centre the Nembe City Stadium, Southern Ijaw has Amassoma, Azuazama, Oporoma. Kolokuma-Opukuma has Kaiama and Opukuma as centres.<br><br><br>In a related development, the draws for round of 32 fixtures in the ongoing Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament have been concluded.<br><br><br>The opening fixtures of the round, will see Apret FC of Imiringi face-off with last year\'s finalist Odioma United while former Ogbia Champions, Movers FC of Otuasega will square off with Moses FC of Sangana by 3pm at the Nembe centre.<br><br><br>Okodi FC who knocked out Anyama FC to qualify from the Otuokpoti Centre will entertain Biseni United, as Amassoma United FC faces high scoring De Grace FC at the Swali Centre.<br>The Imiringi centre will also come alive when Kiri-Pogu Owokiri takes on Dream Academy, as high flying NUJ FC welcomes Ikolo FC at 3pm. Buotoru FC of Igbedi at the Tombia Centre will tango with Akenfa FC while enterprising Dream Boys FC of Odi battles Yenegwe FC.<br><br><br>Ebi Amula tutored Agbere FC at the Ebedebiri Army College Centre will be guests to Agge United, as Azagbene Federated Community lock horns with Ofoni United at 3pm.<br>Giant killers Rose of Sharon FC of Ekeki will battle Ayisco FC of Ogboinbiri at the Amassoma Centre, while Onopa FC will have a date with Oporoma FC at 3pm same venue.<br><br><br>Bayelsa United Feeders at the Samson Siasia Stadium face Ayamalem FC at 10am on Saturday, while the early kick-off of the day will see Shegbelite FC tackle Igbogene FC by 8am.&nbsp;<br><br><br>Tournament discovery Everton Academy of Ikolo will have their first acid test of the tournament with a date with high flying Crusaders Feeders FC, Ogbo United FC who eliminated Famgbe FC to progress to the round of 32 square off with Ogbolo FC at the Samson Siasia Sports Complex.<br><br><br>The Round of 32 promises to see more fire cra kers as teams are leaving no stone unturned to get closer to the mega bucks of 5million.', '28 June 2023', '28', 'June', '2023', '2ghq8h7iovmjmhfawdwpfe1ff8bd0bc26e35d625abe212db42ee.jpeg', 1),
(41, 'Prosperity Cup:Biseni United Humiliates Okodi FC To Secure Round 16 Slot', '**Otuasega, De Grace, Odioma United Booked Round 16 Ticket**<br><br>Biseni United on Friday took control of their round of 32 tie against Okodi FC of Ogbia in the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament tagged the Prosperity Cup with a comfortable 4-0 victory in an encounter decided at the Swali centre.<br><br><br>A brace by Celeb Eze on 33 minutes and 46 minutes and Joseph Fobai on 51 as well as a free kick from Tonny Akpagka on 59 was all Biseni United needed to progress to the round of 16 of Nigeria\'s biggest grassroots football.<br>In the other game at the Swali centre, De Grace FC trounced Amassoma United 3-1 to secure a smooth passage to the round of 16 having scored 10-0 against Yenegwe FC in the preliminary round.<br><br><br>At the Nembe centre, last year finalist Odioma United scored two first half goals to book a place in the round of 16, two quick goals from John Bassey on 36 minutes and 37 minute gave the seasiders a 2-1 victory over Apret FC of Imringi.<br><br><br>Joel Enegesi\'s heroic saves moved Movers FC of Otuasega into the next round with a 4-3 victory&nbsp; on Penalties after playing out a 1-1 draw in the regulation time against Moses FC of Sangana at the Nembe centre in what could be described as the eastern derby.<br><br><br>Joel Enegesi saved two penalties to keep his Otuasega side into the tournament having conceded first. Samson Owei had given Moses FC the lead on 8 minute before Godgift Okilo\'s leveller on 55 minutes.<br><br><br>Hostilities will return tomorrow in the round of 32 of the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament as Shegbelegbe FC welcomes Igbogene FC by 8am at the Samson Siasia Stadium while high flying Bayelsa Feeders will keep a date with Ayamalem FC by 10am.<br><br><br>Ogbo United of Ikibiri will square off with Ogbolo FC at 1pm as tournament discovery Everton Academy of Ikolo battles Crusaders Feeders FC of Peretorugbene by 3pm at the Samson Siasia Stadium.', '01 July 2023', '01', 'July', '2023', 'o5o7hhvmyb79qv37pfps8ade15edc687b2dd2161e05eff6f6259.jpeg', 1),
(42, 'Superb Crusaders Feeders FC Humble Ogbo United to Bag Quarter Final Spot.', '*Shegbelite FC Reaches First Quarter Final in History**<br><br>Crusaders Feeders FC seized control of the Bayelsa State Governor\'s Football Tournament tagged the Prosperity Cup title race as Junior Christopher inspired a crucial 4-1 win over Ogbo United of Ikibiri on Wednesday at the Samson Siasia Stadium.<br><br>Junior Christopher scored a hattrick to increase his goal tally to ten goals in the competition same with Peter Christopher of Ogbo United who scored the only goal for the Ikibiri side.<br>The Crusaders pointman opened the floodgate of goals eight minutes into the game from a low cross and set up Great Vincent\'s goal to double the lead for Crusaders Feeders on 17 minute.<br><br>Few minutes later Peter Christopher scored from a spot kick to give Ogbo United a life line but their expectations were cut short on 68 minute when Junior Christopher fired home to compound Ogbo United woes.<br><br><br>Just before the final whistle Junior Christopher capped the victory with a solo effort to make it 4-1 having overpowered tournament revelation Everton Academy of Ikolo 15-0 to clinch the round of 16 ticket.<br><br><br>Earlier in the day, enjoyment boys Shegbelite FC beat resilient Bayelsa United Feeders 3-2 on penalties after playing a 1-1 draw in regulation time in a packed stadium.<br><br><br>More Round of 16 matches will come up on Thursday at the Samson Siasia Stadium, Biseni United will take on De Grace FC at 1pm while the second game sees high flying NUJ FC square up with Dreams Academy School FC by 3pm.', '06 July 2023', '06', 'July', '2023', 'x5yj9m51ikabfckw0zuuc1c247f7c470c6e26379aca3e65ebcdf.jpg', 1);
